Consider the ticking time bomb scenario: Imagine that you are the
head of the local CIA branch. You capture a terrorist suspect who you believe has information about a
nuclear device set to go off in Manhattan later the same day. In fact, you have reason to suspect that
he planted the bomb himself. As the clock ticks down, he refuses to admit to being a terrorist or to
divulge the bomb’s location. Would it be right to torture him until he tells you where the bomb is and how
to disarm it?

